This paper deals with natural language processing and information retrieval techniques applied to spoken meetings. The use of unsupervised topic modeling is a common approach in the field of computational linguistics, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with information retrieval, which is a subfield of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of machine learning algorithms for topic modeling and summarization can also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the identification of relevant information, which is a common problem in the field of artificial intelligence, falling under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
